import JobZImage from "../../../common/jobz-img"; import CountUp from "react-countup"; import React, { useEffect, useState } from 'react'; import SectionCandidateProfileViews from "../../candidate/sections/dashboard/section-can-profile-views"; function EmpDashboardPage() { const [employerData, setEmployerData] = useState(null); const [stats, setStats] = useState({ totalJobPosts: 0, totalApplications: 0, totalMessages: 0, totalNotifications: 0, }); const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true); // Loading state for both data fetches // Fetch employer data and stats when the component is mounted useEffect(() => { const fetchData = async () => { try { // Fetch employer data const employerResponse = await fetch('http://localhost:8080/emploercandidate', { method: 'GET', credentials: 'include', // Include cookies with the request }); if (employerResponse.ok) { const employerData = await employerResponse.json(); setEmployerData(employerData); // Store the employer data in state } else { console.log('Error fetching employer data:', employerResponse.statusText); } // Fetch employer stats const statsResponse = await fetch('http://localhost:8080/employer-stats', { method: 'GET', credentials: 'include', // Include cookies }); if (statsResponse.ok) { const statsData = await statsResponse.json(); setStats({ totalJobPosts: statsData.totalJobPosts, totalApplications: statsData.totalApplications, totalMessages: 28, // Replace with dynamic value when available totalNotifications: 18, // Replace with dynamic value when available }); } else { console.error('Failed to fetch employer stats'); } setLoading(false); // Set loading to false once both data fetches are complete } catch (error) { console.error('Error fetching data:', error); setLoading(false); // Ensure loading is set to false on error } }; fetchData(); }, []); // Empty dependency array ensures this effect runs only once on mount if (loading) { return
